00:31.144 --> 00:33.311
<i>We're fighting
a war to protect Nassau</i>

00:33.313 --> 00:34.979
<i>in which our most effective weapon</i>

00:34.981 --> 00:38.066
<i>is the fear that we can
instill in our enemies.</i>

00:38.118 --> 00:40.902
Everything is dependent upon that gold,

00:40.954 --> 00:44.289
and right now it is sitting in a
fort with no guns and full of holes.

00:44.324 --> 00:46.241
You couldn't figure out
how to repair the fort,

00:46.293 --> 00:48.993
<i>so you lured me into capturing a
ship full of slaves to do the job.</i>

00:49.046 --> 00:51.329
<i>I wonder if you can help
me locate an old friend of mine.</i>

00:51.381 --> 00:53.164
His name is Charles Vane.

00:53.216 --> 00:55.250
<i>I am to set sail
for the West Indies,</i>

00:55.302 --> 00:56.668
the one element I lack

00:56.670 --> 00:58.253
<i>is someone who understands Nassau.</i>

00:58.305 --> 00:59.754
<i>If you agree to be that person,</i>

00:59.806 --> 01:01.423
<i>your sentence will be commuted</i>

01:01.475 --> 01:02.807
<i>and the charges against you released.</i>

01:02.843 --> 01:05.343
Crew of the Walrus, surrender,

01:05.345 --> 01:07.345
and I am authorized to offer you full,

01:07.347 --> 01:09.597
<i>unqualified pardons.</i>

01:09.649 --> 01:12.684
We're not fighting and
we're not surrendering,

01:12.686 --> 01:13.818
so what are we doing?

01:13.854 --> 01:15.566
We're going that way.

01:15.688 --> 01:18.569
That's a ship killer.

